===Noun===
{{en-noun|-|head=[[natural]] [[law]]}}

# {{label|en|philosophy}} An [[ethical]] theory that posits the existence of a law whose content is set by [[nature]] and that therefore has validity everywhere.
# [[law of nature]]; relating to [[natural]] [[phenomena]].

# (law) A philosophical system of legal and moral principles purportedly deriving from a universalized conception of human nature or divine justice rather than from legislative or judicial action; moral law embodied in principles of right and wrong.

